1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Lagging Theory is not simple delay.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Classical models often assume groundwater flux and hydraulic gradient move together.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:17,000
But real aquifers can respond out of phase.

4
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:25,000
Flow paths, storage, drainage, leakage, and hydro-mechanical coupling can make the response asynchronous.

5
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:32,000
A delay shifts a curve. Flux-gradient asynchrony can change the interpreted aquifer.

6
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:36,000
If it changes recovery time, pumping limits, or a design threshold, it becomes an engineering issue.
